The 17 SDGs are divided into 179 targets which outline and give direction to actions that will lead to success in meeting the goals. The targets are followed by indicators that demonstrate success in meeting the goals when achieved. There are nine targets for the third SDG, which aim to ensure healthy lives and promote well-being for all ages (Figure 2
                  ). The target most focused on children is 3.2:
                     By 2030, end preventable deaths of newborns and children under 5 years of age, with all countries aiming to reduce neonatal mortality to at least as low as 12 per 1,000 live births and under-5 mortality to at least as low as 25 per 1,000 live births. (World Health Organization [WHO], 2021, p. 41)
